How login resolution should work:

1. Request hits a domain
        ↓
2. Domain → resolves to AgencyId (slug or custom domain)
        ↓
3. Email + Password lookup scoped to that AgencyId
        ↓
4. Determine Scope → issue JWT with correct claims


JWT claims should carry:
{
  userId,
  scope,        // Platform | Agency | SubAccount
  agencyId,     // always present
  subAccountId  // only for SubAccount scope
}

Agency Owner should also be able to switch into any sub-account without re-logging in (impersonation)
not a login, just a context switch that issues a new short-lived JWT with a specific SubAccountId.